00:02:49.259 --> 00:02:52.059
So there's a lot of input and output components for Shiny.

00:02:52.059 --> 00:02:55.660
So this is a text input, and if I type some text here.

00:02:55.660 --> 00:03:04.800
So there, this input text gets used by the server code here, and it constructs the string

00:03:04.800 --> 00:03:05.800
and returns that.

00:03:05.800 --> 00:03:06.940
And then that gets rendered over here.

00:03:06.940 --> 00:03:07.940
All right.

00:03:07.940 --> 00:03:11.979
So there's other, again, there's other types of inputs, like numeric inputs, similar to

00:03:11.979 --> 00:03:24.380
text input, sliders, checkboxes, if I check it, this value becomes true or false.

00:03:24.380 --> 00:03:25.539
Checkbox groups.

00:03:25.539 --> 00:03:34.740
So I can select multiple items and it'll give me a tuple with all the selected items.

00:03:34.740 --> 00:03:35.740
Text input.

00:03:35.740 --> 00:03:44.699
So like the dropdown box, radio buttons, text areas.

00:03:44.699 --> 00:03:48.979
So this is for multi-line text input.

00:03:48.979 --> 00:03:55.699
And there's date inputs and date ranges and password.

00:03:55.699 --> 00:04:01.940
That's where it will hide it in the browser, but that value gets sent to the server.

00:04:01.940 --> 00:04:03.179
So that's some of the inputs.

00:04:03.179 --> 00:04:09.660
So for the outputs, oh, this is actually the same app as the input, because you type

00:04:09.660 --> 00:04:15.139
in something and then it sends it back to the, it sends the output back to the web browser.

00:04:15.139 --> 00:04:16.859
So there's actually two varieties of this.

00:04:16.859 --> 00:04:20.820
There's the text output, and this is sort of normal HTML text.

00:04:20.820 --> 00:04:28.940
The verbatim text output, where it returns it as code, or sorry, code formatted text.

00:04:28.940 --> 00:04:35.899
There's UI outputs, which let you display any sort of user interface components as HTML.

00:04:35.899 --> 00:04:41.140
This component here, this text input, is actually output generated dynamically in the server

00:04:41.140 --> 00:04:42.779
and then sent to the browser.

00:04:42.779 --> 00:04:49.299
So that's the UI that's being sent over.

00:04:49.299 --> 00:04:51.459
And plot outputs.

00:04:51.459 --> 00:04:57.500
So if you need to display tables, currently you can use a UI output and if you've got

00:04:57.500 --> 00:05:01.739
a pandas data frame, you can have it generate a table with a two HTML method on those data

00:05:01.739 --> 00:05:02.739
frames.

00:05:02.739 --> 00:05:07.619
But hopefully by the, you know, in near future, we'll have a proper render table output.

